         <abstract>
            <p>The main purpose of this paper is the calculation of the critical determinant, and therefore the packing constant, for any centrally symmetric octahedron. The results are obtained partially by a numerical computation that is not rigorous. As an application, we prove that the lattice of integer vectors perpendicular to any integer vector &lt;latex&gt;$\mathbf{n} = \lbrack n_1, n_2, n_3, n_4\rbrack (0 \leq n_1 \leq n_2 \leq n_3 \leq n_4, n_4 &gt; 0)$&lt;/latex&gt; contains a nonzero vector m ∈ Z&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt;, the height (h(m) = max |m&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt;|) of which satisfies \begin{align*} &amp;\text{(i)} h(\mathbf{m}) &lt; (\frac{4}{3} h(\mathbf{n}))^{1/3} \text{if} n_4 \leq -2n_1 + n_2 + n_3, \\ &amp;\text{(ii)} h(\mathbf{m}) &lt; (\frac{27}{19} h(\mathbf{n}))^{1/3} \text{in any case}, \\ &amp;\text{(iii)} h(\mathbf{m}) \leq h(\mathbf{n})^{1/3} \text{if} n_4 \geq n_1 + n_2 + n_3.\end{align*} The closing examples show that the above estimations cannot be improved.</p>
          </abstract>
